org.azyva.dragom.model

Interface Node

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClassificationNode, Module, MutableClassificationNode, MutableModule, MutableNode

    public interface Node
    Represents a node at runtime.

    Two type of Node's exist each represented by a different sub-interfaces:

    • ClassificationNode
    • Module
    Author:
    David Raymond

      • getNodePlugin

        <NodePluginInterface extends NodePlugin> NodePluginInterface getNodePlugin(Class<NodePluginInterface> classNodePlugin,
                                                                           String pluginId)
        Gets the specified NodePlugin for this Node.

        The NodePlugin must exist. isNodePluginExists(java.lang.Class<? extends org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.NodePlugin>, java.lang.String) can be used to verify if a NodePlugin exists before getting it.

        Type Parameters:
        NodePluginInterface - NodePlugin interface.
        Parameters:
        classNodePlugin - Class of the NodePlugin.
        pluginId - Plugin ID to distinguish between multiple instances of the same NodePlugin.
        Returns:
        NodePlugin. The type is as specified by classNodePlugin.

      • registerListener

        <NodeEventClass extends NodeEvent> void registerListener(NodeEventListener<NodeEventClass> nodeEventListener,
                                                         boolean indChildrenAlso)
        Registers a NodeEventListener.

        The NodeEventListener is registered within the Node, and thus within the Model. It is also possible to register NodeEventListener's in the ExecContext.

        Type Parameters:
        NodeEventClass - NodeEvent class.
        Parameters:
        nodeEventListener - NodeEventListener.
        indChildrenAlso - Indicates if NodeEvent raised on children should be dispatched to the NodeEventListener.

      • raiseNodeEvent

        void raiseNodeEvent(NodeEvent nodeEvent)
        Raises a NodeEvent.

        The NodeEvent is dispatched to all registered NodeEventListener's interested in it.

        NodeEventListener's registered in the ExecContext using EventPlugin.registerListener(org.azyva.dragom.model.Node, org.azyva.dragom.model.event.NodeEventListener<NodeEventClass>, boolean, boolean) are also considered.

        The NodeEvent sub-interface (ModuleEvent or ClassificationNodeEvent) must match the type of Node.

        The NodeEvent must be dispatched on NodeEvent.getNode().

        Parameters:
        nodeEvent - NodeEvent.

      • isCreatedDynamically

        boolean isCreatedDynamically()
        Returns:
        Indicates if the Node was created dynamically. This generally means that it is not based on a NodeConfig and is inferred from some external system.
